<span id="freeTextContainer7876387492087936131">Kind of disappointing overall, but that&apos;s a relative opinion. I&apos;m pretty sure the value of this rises in direct proportion to how little time the reader has spent cooking &amp; learning about food prior to picking this up, and how much patience one has for the story part of recipe blogs. After a few pages the tone goes from breezy to grating fast. Yes, it has useful information even for experienced cooks, but it doesn&apos;t really feel &quot;indispensable.&quot;<br/><br/>Also, omitting garlic and adding ginger instead to t</span>
  <span id="freeText7876387492087936131" style="display:none">Kind of disappointing overall, but that's a relative opinion. I'm pretty sure the value of this rises in direct proportion to how little time the reader has spent cooking &amp; learning about food prior to picking this up, and how much patience one has for the story part of recipe blogs. After a few pages the tone goes from breezy to grating fast. Yes, it has useful information even for experienced cooks, but it doesn't really feel "indispensable."<br /><br />Also, omitting garlic and adding ginger instead to the list of Eastern European spice pantry staples is laughable and criminal. Minus one star just for that.</span>
